text.tspan: Antidepressant drug consumption per 1,000 people vs. GDP per capita,
Daily intake of antidepressants per 1,000 people, calculated as the 'defined daily dose'.
Gross domestic product (GDP) per capita is measured in international-dollars which adjusts for inflation and cross-country price
Data source: OECD Health Statistics, Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank
